Which of the following statements will correctly create and initialize an array
of Strings to non null elements?

String[] sA = new String[1] { "aaa"};
//Array size cannot be given here as the array is being initialized in the declaration.

String[] sA = new String[] { "aaa"};//true

String[] sA = new String[1] ; sA[0] = "aaa";//true

String[] sA = {new String( "aaa")};//true

String[] sA = { "aaa"};//true
